Description: Part of a clay figurine that is rectangular in shape, broken off at both ends. Well smoothed at all preserved sides, almost square in section. The upper side is pierced with holes with a diameter of 0.2cm. The depth is roughly 0.5 to 0.6 cm. Part of a stylized female figurine.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), Mound β, D15.R
